latestPosts.caption:
Still feel dry after using face oil? It might be the type of oil you’re using.

There are two kinds:
🌿 Polar oils mix with water and tend to evaporate quickly, so hydration doesn t last.
🌿 Non-polar oils (like Squalane) repel water, locking in moisture and helping your skin hold onto hydration longer.

How to tell the difference? Try mixing a drop with water in your palm, if it separates, it’s non-polar. If it blends, it’s polar.

Save this for your next trip to @sephora, your skin barrier will thank you.
